
Q1: SQL Set Operation UNION
Question:
Get a list of all unique last names from Person.Person and HumanResources.Employee tables.
SQL:
SELECT LastName FROM Person.Person
UNION
SELECT LoginID FROM HumanResources.Employee;

Q2: SQL Set Operation INTERSECT
Question:
Find last names that appear in both Person.Person and HumanResources.Employee tables.
SQL:
SELECT LastName FROM Person.Person
INTERSECT
SELECT Surname AS LastName FROM HumanResources.Employee; -- adjust field if needed

Q3: SQL Set Operation EXCEPT
Question:
Find last names that are in Person.Person but not in HumanResources.Employee.
SQL:
SELECT LastName FROM Person.Person
EXCEPT
SELECT Surname AS LastName FROM HumanResources.Employee; -- hypothetical field
Q4: SQL Join Operation INNER JOIN
Question:
List the SalesOrderID and ProductID for all sales that have a matching product in the Production.Product table.
SQL:
SELECT sod.SalesOrderID, sod.ProductID, p.Name
FROM Sales.SalesOrderDetail sod
INNER JOIN Production.Product p ON sod.ProductID = p.ProductID;
Q5: SQL Join Operation LEFT JOIN
Question:
Get all products and any matching sales. Show products even if they were never sold.
SQL:
SELECT p.ProductID, p.Name, sod.SalesOrderID
FROM Production.Product p
LEFT JOIN Sales.SalesOrderDetail sod ON p.ProductID = sod.ProductID;
Q6: SQL Join Operation RIGHT JOIN
Question:
List all sales and their product names. Include sales even if the product no longer exists in the product catalog.
SQL:
SELECT sod.SalesOrderID, sod.ProductID, p.Name
FROM Production.Product p
RIGHT JOIN Sales.SalesOrderDetail sod ON p.ProductID = sod.ProductID;
